### Key Learnings
- AI doesn't fix broken processes—it amplifies them. Organizations should optimize workflows before automating them with AI.
- Successful AI adoption requires rethinking how work is done, not simply adding AI tools to existing processes.
- Businesses should identify repetitive, high-volume tasks where AI can improve speed, consistency, and operational efficiency.
- AI is most valuable when paired with human judgment, creativity, and strategic decision-making rather than replacing people entirely.
- Building an AI-ready organization involves upskilling employees, encouraging experimentation, and fostering a culture of continuous learning.
- Companies that integrate AI into their core operations while maintaining strong governance and clear objectives will achieve more sustainable competitive advantages.

