### Key Learnings 
- Scaling AI successfully requires designing reliable systems and workflows around the model—not just choosing the best LLM.
- Claude performs best when given clear instructions, structured prompts, and well-defined context, reducing hallucinations and improving consistency.
- AI should be integrated into existing business processes with human oversight, ensuring quality, compliance, and accountability.
- Organizations achieve better results by treating AI as a collaborative teammate that automates repetitive work while humans focus on strategic decisions.
- Continuous testing, prompt refinement, and performance monitoring are essential to maintain accuracy as AI systems evolve.
- Long-term AI success depends on building reusable workflows, documenting best practices, and creating scalable systems that teams can adopt consistently.

